Title : Congenital aneurysm of the muscular interventricular septum.
Date : 1993
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : Cardiac aneurysms are rare in the paediatric age group, and are classified as congenital when the aetiology cannot be demonstrated. We report a 1-year-old patient with a congenital aneurysm of the muscular interventricular septum. Ventricular septal aneurysmectomy was performed successfully.
